HEADWORD: Epispastic
<hw>Ep"i*spas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr.
<?/ to draw to, attract; <?/ to + <?/ to draw: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧pispastique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Attracting
the humors to the skin; exciting action in the skin;
blistering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epispastic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Epispastic
<hw>Ep"i*spas"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An external
application to the skin, which produces a puriform or serous discharge
by exciting inflammation; a vesicatory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Episperm</ent>⟦br⟧
